quated the Doctrine of Separation of powers to the one practiced in the old Oyo empire, where there were in existence the Alarm, Oyo Mesi, t
he Ogboni among other traditional title holders who took charge of the administration of the said empire. There was a manifest undoubted separation of powers between the Alafin who was the head, the Oyo Mesi, and the Ogboni, this brought about the necessa
ry checks and balances, so that power is not concentrated in the hands of the Alafin, which is capable of being misused or abused.
\par He briefly traced the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid2910923\charrsid9131397 Historical Development of Modern Theory of Separation of Powers as being }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid2910923\charrsid9131397 
