ion, the Executive power and the Judicial power}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid2910923\charrsid9131397 . He also justified the need for checks and balances and collaboration of the three arms of government, in the 
discharge of their functions, toward ensuring smooth governance in the interest of the populace that voted them into power and which must reap the dividends of democracy. He also discussed
 the areas of the constitution which make interaction between the three arms inevitable for the successful execution of the provisions of the constitution. Such as declaration of war. He concluded by making recommendations to assist all the operators of t
