\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\insrsid2910923 at 84}}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\cf0\insrsid2910923\charrsid9131397  stated that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\cf0\insrsid2910923\charrsid9131397 
Nigeria is a nation with a chequered history of democratic rule. The pressures mounted on the Nigerian political system since independence created instability in Nigerian polity. Hence the Judiciary could not carry out its roles effectively, the First, Se
c
ond and Third Republics collapsed thus, paved way for the inevitability of military incursions in Nigerian politics, which truncated the Nigerian nascent democracy. They argued that Studies have shown that in a democratic state, separation of powers is in
d
ispensable and the independence of the judiciary is paramount in achieving sustainable democracy. Their study therefore investigated the impact of the separation of powers in achieving sustainable democracy in Nigeria State. Independent Judiciary enhances
 
due process in a democratic state. They further analyze that incidences and court verdicts on issues relating to how the practice of separation of powers enhances the Judiciary to discharge its constitutionally stipulated roles in achieving sustainable de
m
ocracy in Nigeria is convincing. They therefore concluded that separation of powers enhances the efficiency of the Judiciary in Nigeria. They recommend that the consolidation of democracy in Nigeria will depend on the commitment and ability of the Nigeria
 State to take extra measures to ensure that the theory and practice of Separation of Powers, and the Independence of the Judiciary is firmly established, respected and protected. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\cf0\insrsid2910923\charrsid9131397 The concept of \lquote separation of powers\rquote  explained by Wade and Philips,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af39 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f0\cf0\super\insrsid2910923\charrsid9131397 \chftn 
{\footnote\ftnalt \ltrpar \pard\plain \ltrpar\s39\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid9769842 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f31506\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f0\super\insrsid2910923\charrsid12404938 \chftn }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\insrsid2910923\charrsid12404938  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
