\f0\insrsid2910923 London, 1965}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\insrsid2910923\charrsid12404938 ) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\insrsid2910923 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\insrsid2910923\charrsid12404938 . 22}}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\cf0\insrsid2910923\charrsid9131397  means three different things: 
\par i. That the same persons should not form part of more than one of the three organs of Government, e.g. the Ministers should not sit in Parliaments; 
\par ii. That one organ of the Government should not control or interfere with the exercise of its function by another organ, e.g. the Judiciary should be independent of the Executive or that Ministers should not be responsible to Parliament; and 
\par iii. That one organ of the Government should not exercise the functions of another, e.g. the Ministers should not have legislative powers. 
