nny, whereas, tyranny would inevitably collapse in the presence of a fair and Independent Judiciary. Failed tyranny would probably give way to democracy. The theory and practice of separation of powers is the premise upon which independent judiciary predi
cates, that over time will necessitate the inevitable collapse of dictatorial leadership and tyranny, thus, enthrones the rule of law for good governance and sustainable democracy. 
