 Independence protects the judicial institution from the executive and from the legislature. As such, it lies at the very heart of separation of powers. It is well accepted among advocates of judicial independen
ce that the following are the key indicators of an independent judiciary: 
\par i. Appointment and removal process of judicial officers 
\par ii. How the judiciary is funded 
\par iii. Extent of individual and institutional freedom from unwarranted interference with the judicial process by the executive and legislative arms of government.
\par The role of the Judiciary on maintaining sustainable democracy can be succinctly illustrated using incidences of election and impeachment sagas of Governors Peter Obi and Rotimi Chibuke Amaechi.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af39 \ltrch\fcs0 
