\par For the judiciary to be seen as independent, the way in which Judges are appointed and subsequently promoted are crucial to their inde
pendence. They must not be seen as political appointees, but solely rather for their competence and political neutrality. The appointment of top judicial officers in Nigeria is made by the President on the recommendation of the National Judicial Council (
NJC) subject to the confirmation of the Senate at the Federal level.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af39 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f0\cf0\super\insrsid2910923\charrsid9131397 \chftn {\footnote\ftnalt \ltrpar \pard\plain \ltrpar
