\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\cf0\insrsid4683982\charrsid9131397 This work has examined the three (3) arms of government as a concept of institution and also considered the nature of an independent organ with the travail of an unborn child. 
\par The insistence on checks and balances with substantial l
evel of independence of the arms of government was prioritized. It is however noted that each organ of the government should act within the ambit of its constitutional goals and maintain a level of sanity to avoid conflict or interference with the other a
rms. While we insist on horizontal separation of powers as the best practice in Nigeria, there should be a fair level of checks and balances across the three (3) arms of government. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\cf0\insrsid4683982\charrsid11557203 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f0\cf0\insrsid11557203 4.2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f0\cf0\insrsid6190908\charrsid9131397  CONCLUSION }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\cf0\insrsid6190908\charrsid9131397 
\par A fundamental principle undergirding the design of modern 
governments is that of the separation of powers. However, this research work has stated that the doctrine of separation of powers can only function properly where there is an interplay of checks and balances. By this interplay, the fiction is that, each a
r
m shall be autonomous within its own sphere. This is a fiction properly so called because the three arms of government are by the Constitutional framework expected to operate an overlapping system of administration. Each must carry on in a manner that is 
c
omplimentary to and not subversive of the other two towards peace and good government. This practice however is fraught with challenges in Nigeria. This research work has addressed these challenges. In the course of this study also, the researcher has est
ablished the roles each arm of government play}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\cf0\insrsid1015078\charrsid9131397 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\cf0\insrsid6190908\charrsid9131397  in checking the activities of the others. 
\par Equally, the researcher has posited that members of the executive and legislative organs of government pledge their loyalties to their respective parties and not to t
he electorates to the detriment of the citizens. It is in light of this that the researcher submits that, in spite of structural deficits and some other problems, constitutionalism still holds a better prospect for political stability in Nigeria, if the f
actors that promote these challenges can be attenuated.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\cf0\insrsid9505595\charrsid9131397 
